The paper deals with multi-task learning in Artificial Intelligence, which is a subfield of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions distillation-based learning, which is a popular technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed framework uses active learning principles, which is a subfield of Robotics (cs.RO). The experiments are conducted on Atari 2600 games, which is a popular benchmark in Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper also mentions Reinforcement Learning, which is a subfield of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
